    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Many Lessons of Whitewater</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Theirn Scott letter says Pres and Mrs Clinton used delay and obfuscation in highly effective way to thwart Whitewater investigation</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Whitewater Verdict'' (editorial, Sept. 21):</p>
        <p>I disagree with your conclusion that one of the lessons learned ''is that full disclosure from the outset would have been much the wiser course for the Clintons.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Whitewater Verdict'' (editorial, Sept. 21):</p>
        <p>I disagree with your conclusion that one of the lessons learned ''is that full disclosure from the outset would have been much the wiser course for the Clintons.''</p>
        <p>On the contrary, delay, obfuscation, disingenuousness and brazen constitutional challenges, when coordinated with a highly effective offense intended to demonize your opponents, and coupled with a press corps that seems biased toward Democrats, works like a charm, if you're a Democrat.</p>
        <p>THEIRN SCOTT  Lawrenceville, Ga., Sept. 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
